<dl id="n11140h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11140h">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11140h"> 140(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> tree burial <small>Brown</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n11140h"> <li>FW unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Epilogue</b> Cette femme voulait faire s&eacute;cher <mark>le corps</mark> de son fils <mark>sur les branches d&apos;un arbre</mark>, selon la coutume indienne, afin de l&apos;emporter ensuite aux tombeaux de ses p&egrave;res. <br><font color="green">[This woman wanted to dry the corpse of her son on the branches of a tree, according to the Indian custom, in order to bring it afterwards to the tombs of his fathers.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) I, <i>Atala</i> 78</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Cf. 088.02 (472-160 JJA 46:037) I.4:1A.3 </mm> </dd></dl>
